We had such a beautiful day together. üôåüèºüíï
You might have seen in my story today that I‚Äôm really putting a lot of effort into being more conscious and in the present moment in attempt to get out of my own head. I‚Äôm an over thinker and sometimes it gets to the point where my thinking drives me crazy and makes me extremely overwhelmed. So I had to take control and make changes where I could, and some of those changes are appreciating each day and every little moment, rather than looking at the big picture and getting overwhelmed with what I have to do tomorrow, next week, next month etc. I‚Äôm focusing on my breathing, deep diaphragmatic breaths in and slow exhales. When I breathe I imagine breathing in positive air that rejuvenates me and I breathe out any toxic stuff that I may have going on inside my head. This is something I visualise of course haha! But it helps! 
I‚Äôm also spending a lot more time outdoors in the fresh air, in nature and of course spending quality time with Mia and Dec. I really try to be in the present moment and absorb everything that‚Äôs going on around me. I‚Äôm conscious of things happening in my body, my breathing, my heart beating and my muscles when I move and I can feel the blood going to every cell in my body. Focusing on these things really takes my mind off everything else. And it helps me to be calm and peaceful. I also realise that I exaggerate and over complicate every little challenge to be bigger and harder than they truly are and doing these practices every day help me to simplify everything in my head so I can be calm, logical, rational and ultimately happier. ü§ó
.
Do any of you suffer from anxiety or feelings of overwhelm? What are some things you do every day to help keep yourself in check and not let your thoughts hijack your happiness? .
.
#15monthsold #destress #gratitude #appreciation #emilyskye #fitfam

I had a full blown melt down today - tears and all... and initially the thought of sharing this scared the sh*t outta me! ‚ÄúWhat will people think, can I handle the judgements, what will so-and-so say‚Äù... But then I thought about what would help me right now and if I were to see this from someone else, I‚Äôd definitely feel comforted in some way and at least not so craaaaazy haha! ü§™ I also believe there is power in vulnerability and strength is showing weakness so here it is! üí™üèº And yep, I‚Äôve been in my PJ‚Äôs with my matted ‚Äúmum bun‚Äù all day and it felt gooood! ü§£üôà
.
It‚Äôs almost impossible to open Instagram without seeing contrived perfection or perceptions of perfection in your feed and in my opinion a lot of it is BS! Sometimes it can inspire us sure, but I believe a lot of the time it‚Äôs not real and just makes us feel sh*tty and inadequate. The last thing I‚Äôd ever wanna do is make any of you feel like that with any of my posts. 
Sure, I might sometimes ‚Äúappear‚Äù like I live a perfect life, have it altogether and totally killing life in all areas and I may even be someone‚Äôs idea of ‚Äúperfection‚Äù, but I can assure you, I‚Äôm far from it in all ways. 
I don‚Äôt always have it altogether, I have insecurities, I have times when I have melt downs, doubt myself, feel unmotivated, insecure, feel like I‚Äôm incapable as a mother, business owner, partner.. etc! 
Maybe some of you feel similar at times and feel like you‚Äôre the only one who feels like this, but I‚Äôm here to tell you that you‚Äôre not alone... there‚Äôs at least one other person out there that feels this way (and that‚Äôs me haha üòù) - in all seriousness though, you are not abnormal and you are definitely not on your own.
If you‚Äôre having a crap day or week know that we ALL have crappy times and it will pass and you‚Äôll get through it. Also, please don‚Äôt ever feel ashamed to seek help. I‚Äôm usually someone who bottles up all my sh*t and I try to work it out on my own but I‚Äôve finally reached out for support and that first step is the hardest but oh so good! üôåüèº It‚Äôs a step in the right direction. ‚ò∫Ô∏è
You ARE strong, capable, worthy and loveable. - You better believe it beautiful people!! ‚ò∫Ô∏è Sending LOTS of love to you all. üòò

‚ÄúI don‚Äôt want to get bulky‚Äù, ‚ÄúI just want to grow my glutes and nothing else‚Äù ‚ÄúI gain muscle really fast so I can‚Äôt lift weights‚Äù....
Every day these are things I hear from women. So many women are still afraid of lifting heavy weights and they seem to have this obsession with growing a big booty without growing their legs. It‚Äôs impossible to grow your glutes without growing your quads and hamstrings as well. They‚Äôre all connected and they all work together so there is absolutely no way to isolate just the glutes and to train them intensely enough to stimulate growth without the legs also working and growing. If it were possible to just strengthen and grow the glutes and not the legs you‚Äôd actually have trouble standing and walking as you‚Äôd be so unbalance!!
Sure there are exercises at target the glutes and they‚Äôre very effective at strengthening the glutes but you still work other muscles as well. 
Something I see a lot is women complaining that their legs are really bulky from lifting weights but the thing is generally these women have fat  sitting on top of the muscle so it may appear that their legs are ‚Äúbulky‚Äù but it‚Äôs just that they‚Äôve still got a layer of fat hiding their ‚Äútoned‚Äù legs. Also just for your info ‚Äútoned‚Äù actually means having muscle and little body fat. üëçüèºüòâ
An example is, when I had gained a lot of fat during my pregnancy my legs looked a lot bigger than what they are now and that‚Äôs because I was holding a lot more fat on them so they may have looked ‚Äúbulkier‚Äù. Once I got rid of a lot of the fat that sits on top of the muscle my legs appeared a lot slimmer. Personally, I love muscle and I‚Äôm trying to build more! üòÉ  I just thought I‚Äôd share the truth about weight lifting, muscle and growing your glutes. üòâ Dont be afraid of the muscle ladies, being strong is AWESOME! üòÉüí™üèº
.
.
